Brassica oleracea var. gongyloides

   [2220.gif]
    Authority
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Capparales:Cruciferae
     Synonyms   Brassica caulorapa
   Common names Kohlrabi
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 2220

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A herbaceous plant with an edible swollen stembase,
   with attached leaves. The stem may be up to 10 cm in diameter and may
   be white, green or purple when fully developed. The leaves often have a
   waxy appearance. USES The stem is cooked and eaten as a vegetable and
   the leaves are eaten like spinach. GROWING PERIOD Biennial, normally
   grown as an annual. May be harvested 50-70 days from transplanting.
   COMMON NAMES Kohlrabi, Kohl-kohl, Turnip-rooted cabbage, Chou-rave,
   Kalrabi, Colirrambano, Koolrabi, Choux-raves, Cavolo-rapa, Colirabano,
   Kalrabbi. FURTHER INF Scientific synonymes: B. caulorapa Pasq., B.
   oleracea L. var. Caulorapa communis DC., B. oleracea L. caulorapa DC.
   Koklrabi can be grown fairly well at low elevations in the tropics but
   the highest yields are obtained from plants grown above 800 m with a
   variation of at least 5Â°C between day and night temperatures. Yields
   are normally between 20-24 t/ha or 2-2.4 kg/m2.

   Sources
   SOURCES (B. oleracea L. var. gongylodes L.)
